40|$|<b>Tube</b> <b>worms</b> and phytobenthic assemblages {{in three}} infralittoral and shallow circalittoral Mediterranean benthic {{communities}} developed between 5 and 35 m depth at Punta del Lazzaretto (Giglio Island, Central Thyrrenian sea) were investigated. Despite being three algae-dominated habitats, these displayed different covering {{both in terms}} of algal layers and algal morphologies, reflecting different structural organizations. Twenty-eight serpulid taxa have been reported, increasing both diversity and density values from most photophilic to most sciaphilous habitats. Multivariate analyses showed how algal thalli and <b>tube</b> <b>worm</b> assemblages were strongly correlated; substrata are influenced both physically and biologically, providing different conditions for <b>tube</b> <b>worm</b> settlement...|$|R
