50|$|<b>Tube</b> <b>worms</b> of the Pogonophora family thicket {{the largest}} vents on Axial Seamounts, forming colonies up to 6 m2 thick in places; smaller, less nutritious vents feed {{bacterial}} mats, smaller <b>tube</b> <b>worms,</b> and limpets. The three most common microbial groups are bacterial epsilonproteobacteria, archaeon thermophilics of the Methanococcus family, and archaeons of the Euryarchaeota family. The most common flora at Axial Seamount's hydrothermal vents is the worm Ridgeia piscesae, which is found at hydrothermal sites of all descriptions on the Juan de Fuca ridge, {{and is the}} base of Axial Seamount's hydrothermal ecosystem. Other species on the seamount include the <b>tube</b> <b>worm</b> P. palmiformis, the sea snail Lepetodrilus fucensis, the bristle worm Amphisamytha galapagensis, and the sea spider Sericosura verenae.|$|R
